  "summary": "Frankie experiences a sudden insight regarding the death of Mr. Savage. She theorizes that Basington-French impersonated Savage to sign a fraudulent will before a lawyer and two witnesses who did not actually know the real man. Frankie suspects the real Savage was drugged and hidden in an attic for twelve hours, after which he was administered triethylamine to ensure he would be found dead the following morning. To prove this theory, Frankie suggests authenticating the signature or re-questioning Mrs. Pratt, though she notes that Mrs. Pratt may have been chosen as a witness specifically because of her lack of intelligence.\n\nTo advance their investigation, Bobby and Frankie seek information on Evans, the former parlor maid at Tudor Cottage. At a post office, the postmistress reveals that Evans, formerly Gladys Evans, has married and moved to Wales, where she is now known as Mrs. Roberts. They discover her current address is the Parsonage in Machabert, Wales. Realizing they have overlooked this crucial lead, they decide to travel home immediately. Frankie provides Bobby with money to settle Baz's debts, suggesting her father might purchase Baz's auto repair shop.\n\nDriven by urgency, the pair drives to Medshaw Airport, where Frankie arranges a plane through Donald Gold to reach Wales quickly. They arrive at the vicarage in Machabert as the sun sets and encounter Moira, who appears distressed. Moira confirms she has also discovered the truth regarding Evans, but when Bobby invites her inside, she hesitates and steps back.",
